metadata.description:
Violet fog envelops the city's light  
A shroud of mist that blurs the sight  
Of towering skyscrapers and bustling streets  
A metropolis that never sleeps

A blur of poor choices and missed opportunities  
That left me feeling blue and lost

But in the violet fog, there is hope  
A chance to start anew, to rebuild and cope  
To let go and embrace the present  
And create a future that is worth living

So let the violet fog wrap around me  
A reminder of the past, but also a key  
To a brighter tomorrow, free from regret  
A new life that I won't forget
